There are other countries as well.
"We have difficulties to force companies to remove the banners," confirms Jiří Klása, head of the transport department of the regional office in České Budějovice, whose colleagues are addressing similar stories.
According to Klása, a leaky law is to blame, which binds officials.
First, he has to reach out to the billboard owner in order to put the ad away.
However, company bosses are often unrivaled or know the trick that Aktuálně.cz described in the past when it became more interested in the issue: just move the mobile stand with advertising a few meters and officials can throw the previous call for the removal of black advertising in the trash.
