According to RSD spokeswoman Nina Ledvinová, the company did not respond to repeated written calls for removal, and the case will thus be brought to the table by regional and then probably municipal officials.
Commerz Billboard is one of those suspicious companies that can't get in touch.
It does not accept mail and the official seat in Žižkov was cancelled more than six years ago.
It's not even clear who's behind it.
In the past, the post office of the company went to the South Bohemian entrepreneur Anton Fischer, who was famous for a sharp dispute with the head of the Czech representation of the Hyundai brand.
However, Fischer, whose company, Euro Billboard, leases space from Comerz Billboard and offers it to advertisers, has rejected any connection in the past.
This spring, when ŘSD became interested in advertising for Lipno at the initiative of Aktuálně.cz, Fischer had civil servants send a letter to the mysterious Commerz Billboard to his pension, where the company is reportedly based.
Even from this address, however, no one has contacted the highway administrators to this day.
A futile fight.
Similar silences or opaque changes of residences are not uncommon.
A few years ago, we gradually fined one company two million crowns.
He changed his name and address and there was nothing to do.
The bailiff's case came back, the ads stood on, maybe in other places.
We are quite powerless against such companies and their business practices.
It's like fighting windmills, admits on condition of anonymity one of the officials.
No one has addressed the law in this regard yet.
He spoke to several members who were interested in the issue.
So far, they have not engaged in any activity.
On the contrary, there were MPs who wanted to extend the deadline for maintaining billboards at major Czech roads.
The government rejected it.
