In 2014, they started to prepare the Shippansee LTD application, which uses already planned trips between the world’s capitals, mainly by plane, to transport packages.
In 2015, they commissioned a project to process a company that created applications for MALL.cz, Jobs.cz or ČSFD.
Programming took three quarters of a year and the app was launched in March 2016.
The Převezu application was started in December last year and released in May this year.
It is a local version of Shippansee adapted for the Czech market.
The application was developed by Mesík and Mesík Profi since this January and made available to users at the end of July 2016.
The intention was to do all these applications from the beginning, which will one day merge into one.
In the Czech Republic, they want to fine-tune the application and then, in cooperation with a strong investor, focus more on the global market.
The sharing economy has been a topic lately, and this is a service like AirBnB or Uber.
Aren’t you worried about working in an area that no one can tell you much about yet, where there is a border of sharing and where there is a grey economy?
It’s the same, just a different product.
It is clear to us that if this is successful and we go up with it, we will be another thorn in the side of the grey economy.
But even if someone saves and someone earns, the intention is not to bypass the tax authorities and tax controls.
Every user, on one side or the other, will be encouraged to tax their income if they make income from it.
How do you think the service has so much potential?
The shipper saves and the ferryman earns, respectively, reduces the cost of the trip.
That's the strong idea that unites interest on both sides.
In the age of social networks, which divide people, we would like this one to bring them closer together.
Good stories can be created, people are happy that they helped someone and they will tell about it.
Maybe someone will bring you forgotten glasses, keys or pills.
People, I think, have been lacking a personal approach for a long time, we say about this application that it is a service of people to people.
So how do you guarantee that the courier won’t run away with the package?
Each user of the application, together with registration, scans his/her identity card and indicates his/her bank account, payment or credit card.
These are the channels that give credibility to service and to man.
Couriers also collect asterisks based on sender ratings.
We will also offer insurance, we will fine-tune the details.
The courier is liable for uninsured shipment in case of loss or damage, but does not assume liability for the contents under criminal law if there is something illegal inside and he is not aware of it.
If he is stopped by the police and finds a machine gun or ten kilos of hashish in a sealed package in his trunk, criminal responsibility falls on the sender.
Is there a risk of misuse of sensitive data from the database?
Registered users are, if necessary, traceable by an administrative authority, which will be the only one able to see it, even we ourselves are not able to see them, the data are protected against misuse.
How much money will the courier get after successful delivery?
The courier sets the price and gets the full amount he asks for.
The sender will be charged a few extra percent for arranging the contact.
This money is our profit, but it's only a few percent, because we want to push the volume.
Also, no one can accuse the courier that he did not deliver the package when he actually delivered it, the receipt and delivery are verified using QR codes.
Are there any restrictions?
Whether in terms of the size or the content of the package?
You can transfer anything.
We have three sizes, small as a cube of butter, medium as a plato of eggs and large as a bass of beer.
After that, there are no more restrictions and if someone has a place in the car, they can transport the refrigerator.
Plus, the sender has the option to take a picture of the package in the application, so the courier can see what he wants.
You don’t even have to pack things if you don’t want to hide the content.
You put the forgotten sweatshirt in the courier's hand and that's it.
Who came up with the idea and how long did it take to launch the service?
My friend got the idea more than two years ago, and I didn't pay much attention to it at the time.
Then he showed me a demo application with a transnational reach that targets mainly air passengers.
At that moment I told him that I would not look for an investor, but I would like to become one myself and put my savings into it.
It took another year of development before we founded Shippansee LTD in London due to the greater credibility of the entire product.
This is not the version you are focusing on.
No, we focused our marketing on the Czech Republic, where we are trying to improve the application, because it all had birth pains and there is still something to solve and improve.
We try to respond to customer feedback and we do not deal with the foreign market so much at the moment.
We know it’s a long run, but we don’t want to, we want to create a really good product for people.
Shippansee LTD was the basic and most expensive application, the other two were kind of upgrades.
The transfer was made when we said that the national segment could be much more interesting and that we would at least learn it in the Czech Republic.
