But it can send a package to the exact address to the other end of the world.
It works for senders as well as transport, but the difference is that in it as a courier you can see shipments in the form of points on the map that are closest to you, thanks to the geolocator in your mobile.
Applications for couriers who want to make a living with it, we have called the City of Profi.
So someone can make a fortune picking up packages around town?
Exactly, the last application will be downloaded in Prague by a taxi driver, a student, a mother on parental leave, someone who wants to make the most of their trip to work.
Now that everyone's fooling around with the Pokémon, they can collect this just the same.
One sees where the orders are around the city, comes to it, clicks and sees when it must be delivered and transports the shipment.
It’s cheaper than competitive services.
At the moment, we are still doing a web interface, which will be crucial for companies to send shipments, they will fill in data about them on the web, that is, they will create points on the map.
We are then able to invoice them for the use of the service every month.
Are you working on the project full-time?
It's exhausting, but it's normal for us to work so that we can support and develop the project.
There is no strong multinational investor behind us, we are two guys, one of whom had a brilliant idea and the other jumped into it with other suggestions and ideas.
Now we are looking for an investor strong enough to handle not the Czech market, but who should go with us to a global product and become another huge player on the market like AirBnB and Uber.
