I watched the whole thing.
He was going to work regularly at 3:30, so she always left at 3:00 to go shopping.
She tried every day to see him.
Later, I found out they were meeting in his house, in the laundry room.
How many times have I known they were there?
I got the keys, he was determined I'd catch them there.
But I don't know why, in the end I always stayed at home.
I've never been able to go there, take that decisive step.
You may laugh at me, but I believe my wife controlled me mentally.
I think she soon found out I was controllable, that I was going to do what she wanted.
And I did.
Maybe I'm just a weasel.
My neighbors told me they knew it too.
I was so stupid, I never asked them what to do.
I was afraid that if it all broke, it would be bad.
In the family, only my daughter knew.
So I always put it off, on and on.
One day I went to his apartment to ask for help in the laundry.
He went with me, and I told him that I had received an anonymous message, that he was seeing my wife, and that it was all in evidence.
I asked him what he would say.
He stood there, shrugged his shoulders, looked down at the ground and didn’t say a word.
Then I met his wife on the way from the store.
I told her, but she didn't believe it.
She didn't react to it, and she didn't say anything to me either.
Nobody told me anything back then.
I'm the kind of person who's never been around much, who has trouble meeting people, let alone finding a woman.
So I didn't even think about divorce.
I kept counting on it to end one day.
I thought I'd forgive her and life would go on.
It wasn't like that.
And I've basically never been able to deal with all of this.
I still have it in me to this day.
I used to let her know a lot, but in the end, I gave it up for peace of mind.
He's still living in the next house, and I'm still living with her.
She's just more like my wife my housekeeper.
She always did everything at home - cooking, washing, cleaning.
She's hardworking.
I’ve always wanted to have no other reason to complain.
And you could say she's nice.
But sometimes I want to caress her, hug her, and she won't let me.
We go for walks and shopping together, and everyone thinks we have a happy marriage.
She once told me that she never loved me.
That she loved me and loved me, but that she didn't love me.
And I see that she loves him to this day, he's her god.
And I don't enjoy that kind of life.
