The third reason for the riots is the death of Meles Zenawi.
Zenawi, a former rebel leader, was Ethiopia’s prime minister for 17 years until his death in 2012, when he succumbed to an undisclosed illness.
He was considered a tactical genius, a man who could see around the corner.
Analysts say he was particularly skilled at detecting early signs of discontent, and used envoys to process opponents and win them over to his side.
